OL,3,CFather of man killed in atrocity speak
OL,4,Cof toll of Omagh bomb
OL,6,FThe father of one of those killed in
OL,7,Fthe Omagh bomb attack has spoken of
OL,8,Fthe toll that years of campaigning had
OL,9,Fon his life and family, saying he
OL,10,Fwanted to put faces to the victims.
OL,12,FMichael Gallagher's son Aiden was
OL,13,Fkilled in the 1998 dissident
OL,14,Frepublican car bomb which exploded in
OL,15,Fthe centre of the Co Tyrone town on a
OL,16,Fbusy Saturday afternoon.
OL,18,FAiden, a 21-year-old mechanic, was one
OL,19,Fof 29 people who lost their lives on
OL,20,Fthe day.
