OL,3,CFather of man killed in atrocity speak
OL,4,Cof toll of Omagh bomb
OL,6,FHis father Michael became a
OL,7,F"figurehead" for many of those
OL,8,Faffected by the Omagh bombing after he
OL,9,Fchaired a group set up to help
OL,10,Fgrieving families.
OL,12,FIn the second week of commemorative
OL,13,Fhearings for the victims, Omagh
OL,14,FBombing Inquiry chairman Lord Turnbull
OL,15,Ftold Mr Gallagher that he is known to
OL,16,Fgovernments around the world, as well
OL,17,Fas senior politicians, and was
OL,18,Frecently praised by deputy Irish
OL,19,Fpremier Simon Harris due to his
OL,20,Fcampaigning work.
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@LO]
