OL,3,CFather of man killed in atrocity speak
OL,4,Cof toll of Omagh bomb
OL,6,FMr Gallagher told the inquiry that the
OL,7,Fwork involved a lot of travel and time
OL,8,Faway from his family.
OL,10,FHe also described how it was
OL,11,F"heartbreaking" to watch everyone in
OL,12,Fhis family grieve and that following
OL,13,FAiden's death there was "no joy, no
OL,14,Flaughter" in their family home.
OL,16,FHe said that Aiden's chair remained
OL,17,Fempty, and "part of us empty too".
OL,19,FSpeaking about his campaigning work in
OL,20,Fthe years after the bomb, he said it
OL,21,Ftook over his life.
OL,26,@sD@AOUsD@OO]uD@YOUvD@IO]yD@LOUyD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/17
