OL,3,CFather of man killed in atrocity speak
OL,4,Cof toll of Omagh bomb
OL,6,F"If I have a regret, I would have to
OL,7,Fsay that I would have liked to, and
OL,8,Fprobably should have, spent more time
OL,9,Fwith my own family and less
OL,10,Fcampaigning," he told the inquiry.
OL,12,F"But, it seems to be the way that
OL,13,Fthings worked out.
OL,15,F"We don't have the benefit of
OL,16,Fhindsight but I do think that I would
OL,17,Fpersonally have benefited, and my
OL,18,Ffamily certainly would have benefited,
OL,19,Fif I had done less campaigning.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@MO]tD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/17
