OL,3,CFather of man killed in atrocity speak
OL,4,Cof toll of Omagh bomb
OL,6,F"That's a hugely difficult but honest
OL,7,Fthing that I have to say. If there's a
OL,8,Fconsolation in all of that, it's the
OL,9,Ffact that we are here today, and I've
OL,10,Fsat through all of the testimonies
OL,11,Fthat I've heard, and it has moved me
OL,12,Fenormously.
OL,14,F"I feel to put a human face to the
OL,15,Fperson rather than a statistic, I
OL,16,Fthink that's been one of the
OL,17,Fconsolations, even if we achieve no
OL,18,Fmore than that. But I do hope that we
OL,19,Fwill continue to answer some of the
OL,20,Fvery difficult questions that we
OL,21,Fhaven't had answers to so far."
