OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F441A1738689662
OL,3,CFather of man killed in atrocity speak
OL,4,Cof toll of Omagh bomb
OL,6,F"I don't know whether, and I'm sure
OL,7,Fthat inwardly, she was struggling, but
OL,8,Fshe did manage to hold it together,
OL,9,Fand that was unbelievable, knowing the
OL,10,Fbond that was there between both of
OL,11,Fthem."
OL,13,FMr Gallagher, whose brother was shot
OL,14,Fdead by republican paramilitaries,
OL,15,Fsaid that following the signing of the
OL,16,FGood Friday Agreement, he thought a
OL,17,Fnew chapter was beginning in Irish
OL,18,Fhistory "where people could live
OL,19,Ftogether and play together and enjoy
OL,20,Fand appreciate each other's company".
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@FO]zD@IOU|D@dO]
