OL,6,FSpeaking about the day of the bomb, he
OL,7,Fsaid that he last saw his son at their
OL,8,Ffamily home hours before the blast.
OL,10,FHe said that Aiden left to go into
OL,11,Ftown to meet a friend to buy a pair of
OL,12,Fjeans.
OL,14,FDescribing his last moments with his
OL,15,Fson, Mr Gallagher added: "We had what
OL,16,FI would describe as a pleasant
OL,17,Fconversation. In fact, I remember
OL,18,Ftelling him where to park the car that
OL,19,Fwould be convenient to the shop he was
OL,20,Fgoing to.
OL,26,@wD@ZOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G13/17
