OL,3,CFather of man killed in atrocity speak
OL,4,Cof toll of Omagh bomb
OL,6,F"He turned around and he walked down
OL,7,Fthe hall, and I remember he looked
OL,8,Fback for the last time and he said, 'I
OL,9,Fwon't be long'. And that was really
OL,10,Fthe last time we seen Aiden."
OL,12,FHours later, he was at a makeshift
OL,13,Fmortuary identifying his son's body.
OL,15,FHe said that telling his family that
OL,16,FAiden would not be coming home was
OL,17,F"extremely painful and difficult" but
OL,18,Fthat the response from the public to
OL,19,FAiden's death helped restore their
OL,20,Ffaith in human nature.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@]O]yD@AOUyD@aO]
