OL,3,CFather of man killed in atrocity speak
OL,4,Cof toll of Omagh bomb
OL,6,FHe said he feels that Aiden has never
OL,7,Fleft them and that he has always been
OL,8,Fpart of their family.
OL,10,FAiden's sister Cat Wilkinson said she
OL,11,Fwas "living in turmoil" following his
OL,12,Fdeath.
OL,14,F"I was like a caged animal,
OL,15,Ffrustrated, confused and angry," she
OL,16,Fsaid in her statement to the inquiry.
OL,18,F"My parents could cry together,
OL,19,Freminiscing about old times, I could
OL,20,Fnot. I wish I could, but I still did
OL,21,Fnot believe that he was dead.
OL,26,@sD@EOUsD@WO]vD@AOUwD@`O]zD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G15/17
